<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8744: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-13T19:00:00-04:00">July 13, 1937—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>116. Your 228, July 13, 6 p.m. and Nanking’s 275, July 13, 3 p.m.
                                Department feels it desirable that you remain where you are pending
                                    <pb facs="0163" n="156" xml:id="pg_156"/> further developments.
                                If developments cause you to feel that you should proceed to
                                Nanking, please consult Department.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>